==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warwickite
<hw>War"wick*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A dark brown or black mineral, occurring in prismatic crystals
imbedded in limestone near <etsep>Warwick</etsep>, New York. It consists
of the borate and titanate of magnesia and iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warworn</ent>⟦br⟧
